Geoffrey Tanner Woolley: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 12:39 PM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Patamar Capital



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Geoffrey Tanner Woolley  Chief Executive Officer, Patamar CapitalAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 8 Board Members in 8 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships57--
Background

		Mr. Geoffrey Tanner Woolley, also known as Geoff Chester, is a Co-Founder and Managing General Partner of Dominion Fund V, L.P. Mr. Woolley serves as the Chief Executive Officer of Patamar Capital. In early 2011, Mr. Woolley co-founded Unitus Impact to support livelihood acceleration in Asia and Africa, prove the viability of investments in livelihood ventures and attract capital markets and other investors to the space. He has been involved in impact investing and microfinance ... since he joined Unitus Labs as a board member in 2001. He also serves as the Chief Executive Officer at Unitus Capital. Mr. Woolley is a Founding Partner and Managing General Partner of Dominion Ventures, Inc. He is a Venture Partner at EPIC Ventures since 2006 and participates in the review, due diligence and oversight of technology investments. Mr. Woolley serves as an Advisor on the Boards of Polaris Ventures, Euclid SR Partners and Von Braun & Schrieber Private Equity. Mr. Woolley founded Kreos Capital in 1997 and served as an advisor to Kreos Capital from its inception. He served as Senior Advisor at CognoLink Limited and Third Bridge Group Limited. Working as an entrepreneur most of his professional life, Mr. Woolley founded both Dominion Ventures, Inc., and European Venture Partners. He has been active in private equity and venture capital investing for over 25 years and founded two successful venture funds in the United States and Europe and has been involved in financing over 300 growth companies, including Bookham, Ciena, Coinstar, Hotmail, Human Genome Science, Tivoli and Vertiex Pharmaceuticals. He serves as Chairman of Board of Directors and Member of Advisory Board at University Venture Fund. He serves as Chairman of Unitus Capital. He served as Chairman of MACC PEI Liquidating Trust from April 2004 to December 2009. He served as Chairman of MorAmerica Capital. He currently serves on several University of Utah advisory boards. He serves as Member of the Advisory Board of Jana Care Inc. Mr. Woolley is also a Director of Utah Capital Investment Corporation, Utah Fund of Funds II LLP and a Member of the Board of Utah Fund of Funds. He serves as a Director of University Impact Fund. He holds Board seats at Micro Benefits China and other social enterprises benefiting those at the base of the economic pyramid. He has been a Director of MACC Private Equities Inc., since 2003. He is a founding and current board member of Samhita Microfinance. He continues to sit on the Board of various entrepreneurial companies. In 1998, he assumed an advisory role at Dominion in order to pursue non-profit and other business interests. His company Directorships includes Brisk Heat and Hild Life Annuity. He has been an Independent Director of Bharat Financial Inclusion Limited since March 22, 2006. He serves as Member of Advisory Committee of Kreos II. He served as Member of Advisory Committee of Kreos Capital III Limited. Mr. Woolley has been active with many worthy non-profits. Mr. Woolley is very active in Eccles Business School at the University of Utah where he chairs a program to make the school a top entrepreneurial business school in the next seven years. Mr. Woolley is active in micro finance with Unitus and works with other non-profit entities. He was active in the 2000 presidential election and took an active “Co-Chair” role in the Gore 2000 campaign. Mr. Woolley served for five years as the Chairman of the NAMES Project and remains engaged in HIV issues. Mr. Woolley pioneered the concept of venture debt and has invested in over 400 companies in his career. He has over 25 years of venture experience. Mr. Woolley also holds an M.B.A. from the University of Utah and a B.S. in Business Management and B.A. in Finance from Brigham Young University.Read Full Background




